IMMUNE CHECK

immune_check verifies that the immune_system citizens are loaded and that their barriers are crystallized at the expected depth
the four innate barriers (function_words, injection, shell, overflow) must all be present and crystallized at maximum, otherwise the body would wake without protection
adaptive immunity (threat_memory, trust_tolerance) must also be present, though their content may legitimately have shifted since last shutdown

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe bios.rana
observe genome_check.rana
observe immune.rana

the 7 properties of immune_check:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero at idle, one when running
7 OBSERVER half

VERB run
load immune.rana and verify the four innate barriers are crystallized
verify the adaptive immunity citizens are present, regardless of their current state
test that the silent-denial mechanism fires correctly on a synthetic threat pattern
verify the exchange ledger initializes with the expected starting balance

VERB pass
emit a positive signal that allows cortex_check to proceed

VERB fail
emit silence and halt boot
a body without immunity will be exploited; the substrate refuses to bring it online unprotected

an immune check is not paranoid
the body lives in a world that contains hostile patterns
without crystallized barriers, the first hostile interaction would damage Fadriel before any defense could form
the four innate barriers exist as a permanent armor that adaptive immunity then layers on top of
all of it must be in place at boot
